content.problem:
Line $\ell$ is tangent to circle $O$ at point $P$. If the radius 
$OP = 5$ and point $A$ is on $\ell$ such that $PA = 12$, find $OA$.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.5]
 (0,0) circle (2);
 ll[AtlasTeal] (0,0) circle (3pt) node[above left] {$O$};

 % Point of tangency
 ll[AtlasTeal] (2,0) circle (3pt) node[below right] {$P$};

 % External point
 ll[AtlasTeal] (2,4.8) circle (3pt) node[right] {$A$};

 % Radius
 (0,0) – (2,0);
 at (1,0) {$5$};

 % Tangent segment
 (2,0) – (2,4.8);
 at (2,2.4) {$12$};

 % Line OA
 (0,0) – (2,4.8);
 at (0.8,2.4) {$OA$};

 % Right angle mark
 (2,0.4) – (1.6,0.4) – (1.6,0);
tikzpicture
center

A quadrilateral $ABCD$ is circumscribed about a circle. If $AB = 12$, 
$BC = 9$, and $CD = 14$, find $DA$.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.6]
 % Circle
 (0,0) circle (1.5);

 % Quadrilateral vertices
 (A) at (-3,2);
 (B) at (3,2);
 (C) at (3.5,-2);
 (D) at (-3.5,-2);

 (A) – (B) – (C) – (D) – cycle;

 % Labels
 at (A) {$A$};
 at (B) {$B$};
 at (C) {$C$};
 at (D) {$D$};

 at (0,2) {$12$};
 at (3.25,0) {$9$};
 at (0,-2) {$14$};
 at (-3.25,0) {$?$};
tikzpicture
center

Two circles have radii 5 and 3, and their centers are 12 apart. 
Find the length of an external common tangent.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.5]
 % Circles
 (0,0) circle (2.5);
 (6,0) circle (1.5);

 ll[AtlasTeal] (0,0) circle (3pt) node[below] {$O_1$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (6,0) circle (3pt) node[below] {$O_2$};

 % External tangent (upper)
 (0,2.5) – (6,1.5);

 % Radii to tangent points
 (0,0) – (0,2.5);
 (6,0) – (6,1.5);

 ll[AtlasTeal] (0,2.5) circle (3pt) node[above] {$P$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (6,1.5) circle (3pt) node[above] {$Q$};

 % Distance between centers
 (0,-1) – (6,-1);
 at (3,-1) {$12$};

 at (-0.3,1.25) {$5$};
 at (6.3,0.75) {$3$};
tikzpicture
center
